here are 3 small things that instantly make a website feel more premium:

    1. lenis scroll
    
    lenis adds a bit of weight to scrolling. not floaty or weird, but smoother and more intentional than default browser scroll. you don’t really notice it the site just feels calmer (if done correctly).
    
    2. view transitions
    
    instead of pages hard-cutting, they ease between states. fades, subtle movement, shared elements. it feels like you’re staying inside the same experience instead of jumping between pages. gives you a SPA feel even for a MPA website.
    
    3. pressed states on buttons
    
    everyone knows hover states. not everyone uses pressed states.
    my go-to is a simple scale(0.99) on press. tiny change, big difference. gives you that clicky ux feedback.
